HB 629 Original 2026 Regular Session Lyons
Abstract: Creates the "Krewe of Athena" motor vehicle special prestige license plate.
Provides for the creation, issuance, design, fees, implementation, distribution, and
rule promulgation applicable to this license plate.
Proposed law requires the Dept. of Public Safety and Corrections to issue a special prestige
license plate to be known as the "Krewe of Athena" license plate, provided there is a
minimum of 1,000 applicants for such a plate.
Proposed law requires that the secretary work in conjunction with the Krewe of Athena
Carnival Club, Inc. to select the color and design of the plate. Requires the design include
the words "Krewe of Athena".
Proposed law specifies that the license plates will be issued, upon application, to any citizen
of La. in the same manner as any other motor vehicle license plate.
Proposed law requires the dept. to collect an annual royalty fee of $25 in addition to the
standard motor vehicle license tax and a $3.50 handling fee for each plate to be retained by
the dept. to offset a portion of administrative costs.
Proposed law requires monies received from the royalty fees be forwarded to the treasurer
of the Krewe of Athena Carnival Club, Inc. Specifies that monies received from the royalty
fees be used to provide scholarships for debutantes.
(Adds R.S. 47:463.243)
